	   <tr><td colspan=2>I have been hunting the pool room (Zone point from CS) for about 2 weeks now, 4 or 5 times a week, 3hrs at a go...I have practically a full suit of Guardian Armour for my Warrior (not that he needs it but the Girdle and shoulders are decent, plus the Legs have good resists)&nbsp;&nbsp;I am after this robe for Enchanter (High Elf in leather look ad keeps gettting asked for Res's..ahem) but have had no luck so far. Anyway some hints on this room.<br><br>- At 52 about 50% of the mobs are blue, 25% cyan and the other 25% green.<br><br>- The Guardians are the only things I have seen that drop the armour, Gargoyles have yet to drop any.<br><br>- Loot isn't bad, average 4pp each, adds up quite fast, some gems (occasional Ruby) a few of the more common drop spells, and Velium pieces (sell well in the bazaar but are heavy)<br><br>- Avoid Suez (Drake) and his friends in the far corner as well as drakes and sentinels in the next room, beyond the portcullis. If the pool room is giving good exp these guys will be a real handful.<br><br>- Gargoyles behind Portcullis (closest to zone point) are single pull-able. Just ease into the room slowly and to one side,  as soon as you see one move, back out. The passage past these is a safe place to camp and bind (so far) There seems to be a mouse targetting problem when in these corridors.<br><br>- The Sentries at the other Portcullis are also single pullable, take them from the right side (so avoiding Suez's gang) take Drahs first then Maof. Make sure you pull Maof to the right side of the room, do NOT run around the right and then over to the left where you zoned in, pathing will mess up and he'll warp past Suez and bring him along for the ride. Suez is a mid 40's Enchanter. Maof is a cleric, in his highest level state (40 at a guess) he can CH. The scond Gaurdian on that side (Salva) is also a Cleric doesn't reach the level to CH...that I have seen yet.<br><br>- Everything in here has innately high MR, especially now after last patch...finding that snares stick more but DoT's get more resists.<br>Tash everything first if you have an Enchanter.<br><br>- Bring any plate wearing Alt's along, if you spend time here you will end up letting bits of armour rot ,maybe also chain wearers too, the Sentry armour is pretty good (although it appears much rarer) some of this is dropable and also sells well.<br><br>- I have seen 2 Breast Plates (rare, apparently) and let rot untold girdles, shoulders and arms (the most common of the drops) I am thinking I may never see a Robe and if I get a Helm for my Cleric (lost one due to Server Crash and Roll Back) then I may just give up...Don't expect to get one within a few hours, of course if you do, then WTG and I hate you :¬) but if you have a group of 51's and under the room will be good exp, not bad loot and you'll max kromzek faction in a week.<br><br><br><br><br><em id=fs8>Edited, Fri Sep  6 10:01:14 2002</em><br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
