	   <tr><td colspan=2>Went dungeon crawling as my Nec needed a Robe update.&nbsp;&nbsp;Hmm, same stats as a FBCR except 2 less to a couple saves, 5 more mana, and STA rather then STR.  Only thing is on a DE it makes you look like you do in an Oracle Robe, different look but not overly flattering.  I put it on a par with an FBCR (doesn't look as good) and much better then an SMR.  FYI the two of us camped about 10 spawn points (mix of Sents and Guardians), probably spent about 8 hours over two nights before one dropped, I was very happy to get out of there.  So we probably killed 70-80 Guardians before it dropped (approx 30 minute spawn), but it was worth it.  And if you are there for EXP many times MOB's dropped 4-6PP per kill, better money then SF or BW.<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
